Follow-up rates for the four post-baseline surveys are shown in Table 2. Attrition occurred when students failed to remember their account details for completing surveys online, were absent from school on the day of the survey, or failed to provide a correct identification code when completing a paper version of the survey. However, as participants could still complete later surveys after an absence, only 69 participants (4%) completed no follow-up surveys. Attrition analyses were conducted to assess differences in outcomes between participants who were lost to follow-up compared to those who remained. Participants who completed no follow-up assessments did not differ significantly from participants who completed at least one follow-up assessment in terms of the proportion using cannabis at baseline (12.3% vs. 5.8%, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
